Rating: 3
Here are things you can do with the flavoring. If you want a milder garlic taste mash minced garlic with a little salt and let it sit for a while, 10 minutes is plenty. If you are using garlic that has a green shoot in the center take that shoot out, it can make the garlic taste bitter. For herbs: certainly, fresh minced mint, cilantro, parsley, chives, etc. are all good. You could lightly toast a little freshly ground cumin and stir it in. Lemon juice would be fine too. A few notes from the recipe author, 15 years later.

