Rating: 3
This was a banner year for cucumber production in my garden, and because of it, I've experimented with a lot of different salad recipes. This is far and away my favourite. I made it with low-fat yogurt, drained overnight so it was dense and thick and clung voluptuously to the diced cucumbers. I skipped the whipping cream, as it seemed entirely superfluous, and added a squeeze of fresh lemon juice instead. Yummy!!

